$interpreted: Sanchez: *whimper*...resisting arrest and breaking into the hatchery...there's no way we're not getting sentenced to death!
Rune: ...death...?
Sanchez: Oh shut it! It's your fault anyway!
Sanchez: Wahhhh!
Prison Guard: Hey! Quiet down in here, you mutts!
Rune: Don't hit...Sanchez!
Prison Guard: Hey! This guy's a beast! I need some help!
Lazer: What's going on?
Prison Guard: General, these two inmates are trying to escape!
Lazer: ...Let me see them.
Lazer: I see you haven't learned your lesson.
Lazer: If you don't behave, I'll beat you senseless. That way you'll remember. How's that?
Sanchez: Gen-General, this is a big misunderstanding! Just one giant, huge, enormous misunderstanding!
Lazer: Misunderstanding? You've murdered your own master. Of course you'd think escaping prison is just a petty crime.
Sanchez: N-N-No! It's not like that! I didn't kill my master!
Sanchez: M-My master is e-e-everything to me. How could I do such a thing?
Sanchez: Scumbag, go ahead and tell the General that we didn't have anything to do with it!
Rune: It was...someone else.
Lazer: Go on.
Sanchez: I-I-I heard...that night...we heard...
Lazer: A group of people in purple cloaks murdered Yusuf, and yet you two managed to get away. Is that what you're saying?
Sanchez: Yes! Yes, exactly! We don't know anything. We're innocent!
Sanchez: G-G-General? Aren't you going to release us?
Lazer: Did I say that?
Sanchez: But we're going to be killed if we stay here!
Lazer: And?
Lazer: I'm here to confirm how the Priest was killed. Whether you live or die is of no concern to me.
Sanchez: General! Please! General──!!
Devious: If it isn't General Lazer? What a pleasant surprise~
Lazer: Surprise? The prison is under my jurisdiction. It's a rare sight to see the High Priest in such a lowly place.
Devious: I obey the sacred edicts of the Snake God. Wherever He leads me, I shall go.
Devious: In any case, this place will soon be washed clean with the blood of martyrs...
Lazer: Blood of martyrs!?
Lazer: Are you saying——
Devious: Indeed.
Devious: ──The Martyrs' Colosseum will soon be reopened.
Devious: The merciful Snake Goddess uses her own blood and body to feed us. We must repay her in kind; with fresh blood, war, and death.
Devious: Prisoners, are you listening?
Devious: To celebrate the completion of the Holy Shrine's renovations and the anniversary of the New City, you will have the honor to fight for the Snake God~
Irate Inmate: Is this a joke? Didn't the Queen abolish that tradition?
Weak Inmate: I only stole a few fruits from a Desert Aqua Tree...how...why...?
Lazer: Did you...threaten the Queen while I wasn't around?
Devious: Hssssss. I merely conveyed to Her Majesty what was told to me by a maid. Lucky for her, nothing happened to the eggs.
Lazer: You...slimy old snake...
Clergy Member: General, restrain yourself!
Devious: Hssssss. Relax, it's nothing~
Devious: Today is a day for celebration. Besides, I'd rather be an old snake...than something that's neither lizard nor human...
Soldier: General! Think of the Queen...!
Lazer: ......
Lazer: ...*sigh*...
Devious: Hssss. Looks like the General needs to take a deep breath.
Devious: Ah~ I just realized that you were right. This place is much too dirty for me.
Devious: I must be going.
Devious: Hsss. See you at the Colosseum...General Lazer~
Lazer: ......
Soldier: General...are we just supposed to sit back and let the High Priest do as he pleases?
